</p></li><li id="LI_51C2CBD2737747D0B2A52FEA03E00762" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Open the top cover 
</p><note type="important" id="GUID-7215619B-4D8E-42B1-B219-10C1EF6B5FB5" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Do not lean on the strip support. 
</p></note></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Move the printhead carriage to the maintenance position or the manual maintenance position 
</p></li><li id="LI_AC6073C6D4BB469F969AC9F3D2DC4343" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Do 
<xref keyref="15DISA024" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-AA5324A1-C2EA-4998-AA67-27200E036856.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 15 How to remove the media input (buffer) cover assembly?>15 How to remove the media input (buffer) cover assembly</xref> 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">For motor (03M4) at the left hand side: 
</p><ul id="UL_1D218E7298594395BB30F898E37E4EDD" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_FDE1775D9F5B4E05BE0CDF567C55BD5D" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Do 
<xref keyref="24DISA027" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-B629596A-B127-4931-8F1D-2869DF89B8C9.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 24 How to open/remove the manual maintenance door?>24 How to open/remove the manual maintenance door</xref> 
</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p ">For motor (03M3) at the right hand side: 
</p><ul id="UL_EBF57181A3C14059AFAB534E4974D4D2" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_63610D4C0F104ABE84FA15FC008010CE" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Do 
<xref keyref="07DISA022" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-2D90D262-D1D0-4062-B2F5-28ED447BF111.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 07 How to remove the maintenance tray assembly?>07 How to remove the maintenance tray assembly</xref> 
</p></li><li id="LI_68FA48997B544822B8DE0E71E5A1C3C4" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Do 
<xref keyref="07DISA024" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-17B27C06-4881-45FC-A784-579CC398D058.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 07 How to remove the maintenance unit?>07 How to remove the Tissue Wipe Unit</xref> 
</p></li></ul></li></ol></prereq><section id="GUID-E4895B67-7FC1-4974-A5C8-D34725505879" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Required tools</title><ul id="UL_87C07BDB1DB343AA8E5C3E5D25BC306F" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_B886592691E14364A61177368F903EAA" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Screwdriver Torx T20 
</p></li><li id="LI_4720CF028339449FA7A1A3B5DD8E31B4" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Socket wrench 10 mm 
</p></li><li id="LI_929C0F12811B4096BB70DA320BD9C6C8" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Protective gloves: 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Microflex</b> 93-260 gloves. 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-C02D66D1-E3CC-4BC2-95F8-775D93D93431" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Warning / Caution</title><note type="caution" id="GUID-A97040BC-F110-4E4B-9CFF-E8082B9DA00E" class="- topic/note "><fig id="GUID-DB340B14-87E5-4FDB-8108-245D16C84FF1" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-FCF86E23-0DD4-40BC-ACDF-FF8ABA1E6502-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-FCF86E23-0DD4-40BC-ACDF-FF8ABA1E6502-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">Avoid skin contact with ink: wear protective gloves. 
</p><fig id="GUID-7C716739-2AD7-42F8-8EF6-B28A8E7B1F76" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-D8099BBE-C3A2-4392-8B56-C532EDDD6073-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D8099BBE-C3A2-4392-8B56-C532EDDD6073-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "> Protect your eyes from splashing ink: wear safety glasses. 
</p></note></section><section id="GUID-EC9C24D5-D455-4022-B616-D7FEF4DE0A1A" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Illustration</title><fig id="FIG_96054265C4C2423DACAFB56A3CDCA3F2" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-BBB65671-5FE2-40E1-93DE-28ED98A8EE2E-low.png" id="IMAGE_88EA1E8B30614E56B2388241DC2AD4D3" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-BBB65671-5FE2-40E1-93DE-28ED98A8EE2E-low.png"/></fig><fig id="FIG_C1D014967E6549A3A979AE6D735E8F98" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-F6CAB207-EA0C-42C6-80DE-7E2071B2B44A-low.png" id="IMAGE_DC728D46034E44DDB1176D9F597B5D6A" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-F6CAB207-EA0C-42C6-80DE-7E2071B2B44A-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="SECTION_54B1129AD8EA41FABFB9D70BBD4CEA51" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">How to remove</title><note id="GUID-1EC09AF2-172D-4532-BCB3-18CAAD0DA91B" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Pictures in procedure are all for 03M4 on the manual maintenance door side of the engine. 
</p></note><table id="TABLE_35E0D923C9564350BF96336D4E5C166A" pgwide="1" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Remove the white spacer. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_6C330181B8F347E797BCB463EC8E6389" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-70C24C45-8D08-49BB-BF27-C2402F4ECB8D-low.png" id="IMAGE_58EA3F7895D04A5185C56E3415B1DD89" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-70C24C45-8D08-49BB-BF27-C2402F4ECB8D-low.png"/></fig><fig id="FIG_D44840AA203B41488F0C5CEF7F421506" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-F472865D-93F4-4353-B0DE-8FB5C73BB259-low.png" id="IMAGE_A7DAD5253146467C8A995D0688ED6A12" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-F472865D-93F4-4353-B0DE-8FB5C73BB259-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Disconnect the connector of the motor. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_EA2DBC52E2AE48F2B32F1FD1D92274CC" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-98517785-EDC0-4379-A95A-4B29DB6B6E92-low.png" id="IMAGE_5CE9E7FD357A4D689D9B9E995C1618A7" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-98517785-EDC0-4379-A95A-4B29DB6B6E92-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the screw (including bushing and ring) at the side of the motor. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_1732C4FEB5D5439A9C312D16894D799C" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-3D6C82ED-33AC-4C92-A426-A8F1F82B55A0-low.png" id="IMAGE_55D9F46120854AD1BCD28FD344D18B03" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-3D6C82ED-33AC-4C92-A426-A8F1F82B55A0-low.png"/></fig><fig id="FIG_FFAECC86EF544A8F820D66A34DBA6892" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-AFD3C896-9D34-4A9C-8A61-7630FD0D6B16-low.png" id="IMAGE_4EC3BC2CCF384C8EB7AD60F38CD03A5B" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-AFD3C896-9D34-4A9C-8A61-7630FD0D6B16-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the clip and the locking pin of the motor. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_FCA77027668244EEB815DD445BC33174" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-F6CAB207-EA0C-42C6-80DE-7E2071B2B44A-low.png" id="IMAGE_D92A592ED54F4B0EBB3992A053184B7A" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-F6CAB207-EA0C-42C6-80DE-7E2071B2B44A-low.png"/></fig><fig id="FIG_B699113D4FDE4E42BD3EABC609506D8C" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-F6209150-FB7C-47AD-A62B-68BD57E43A0F-low.png" id="IMAGE_210E34329F3B4C0C8DB7DAB6C4C94B8F" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-F6209150-FB7C-47AD-A62B-68BD57E43A0F-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the motor to the top. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_1B6B867CAB1447388B80FB3406A42A89" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-BBB65671-5FE2-40E1-93DE-28ED98A8EE2E-low.png" id="IMAGE_E4005F36E2F740DBB1B61CA77518F98A" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-BBB65671-5FE2-40E1-93DE-28ED98A8EE2E-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-234D70A5-41EC-40E2-9E43-4217D346F540" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">How to install</title><table id="GUID-BDB87D50-9E70-4086-AC9E-FA7970C76B0D" pgwide="1" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Install in reverse order. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Reconnect the Service jumper, exit SDS and press 'Restart' on the operator panel. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">In case a 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">new</b> motor is installed: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Do 
<xref keyref="SDS03-8-007" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-00204DD4-8A74-4302-8676-68D7B0265A7A.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 03-8-007 Number of starts of the ZMS motor (Left or Right hand side) [Maintenance Counters]?>03-8-007 Number of starts of the ZMS motor (Left or Right hand side) [Maintenance Counters]</xref> and reset the value for the new motor to 0. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Calibrate: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Do SDS test: 
<xref keyref="SDS21-6-002" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-D650BDBB-4674-4B96-BD64-98FDD9BAF4CB.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 21-6-002 Select required printer calibrations [Special Tests]?>21-6-002 Select required printer calibrations [Special Tests]</xref> and select: <ph translate="no" class="- topic/ph ">Height adjust service </ph>. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Do SDS test: 
<xref keyref="SDS21-6-003" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-B828E436-A124-4809-981E-2DBE1E09A388.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 21-6-003 Execute selected printer calibrations [Special Tests]?>21-6-003 Execute selected printer calibrations [Special Tests]</xref>. 
